rComments: She Taught a very intense course. I feel she did the best at getting us to understand all the info we needed to have an understanding of constitutional law in the short time that she had. Just do your reading and you'll be fine.
Interesting class and she is extremely helpful and always available to talk to you either after lecture or during her office hours! highly recommend her classes!

International law class was interesting and well structured. She is very clear and her lectures were easy to follow. She is extremely helpful and always available to talk to you either during her office hours or after lectures! Highly recommend her!

Lectures were dry, no breaks or anything. Did a pretty good job incorporating relevant current events into the lectures though. In-class midterm with four different hypothetical legal cases where you respond with constitutional issues on each. Good concept but she was looking for a lot more than she prepared us for. Final exam: take home essay.
